		$task->title = "Backup with Plugins";
		$task->body = '<h2>WordPress backup plugins add the element of ease to creating dependable backups for your WordPress site. All you have to do is install your favorite WordPress backup plugin, configure a few settings and you&rsquo;re good.</h2><h3>Duplicator Free WordPress Plugin</h3><p><a title=\"Duplicator\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/duplicator/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-36119\" title=\"How To Backup Your WordPress Site Duplicator WordPress Plugin\" src=\"http://mainwpex.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/how-to-backup-your-wordpress-site-duplicator-wordpress-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"how-to-backup-your-wordpress-site-duplicator-wordpress-plugin\" width=\"750\" height=\"393\" /></a></p><p>With a cool 4.9/5.0 rating and over 500K active installs, <a title=\"Duplicator\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/duplicator/\" target=\"_blank\">Duplicator</a> is more than your typical backup plugin. Primarily, Duplicator helps you to clone or migrate your site to another location easily. This main feature makes it a powerful backup solution.</p><p>Even though it won&rsquo;t allow you to schedule backups, it automatically dumps your database to an SQL file and saves it to a ZIP archive along with your WordPress files. Then it creates a special PHP file that lets you reinstall the backup easily. Just upload the ZIP archive and the PHP file to your server, and the rest is easy work.</p><h3>BackWPup Free WordPress Plugin</h3><p><a title=\"BackWPup\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/backwpup/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-36120\" title=\"How To Backup Your WordPress Site BackWPup WordPress Plugin\" src=\"http://mainwpex.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/how-to-backup-your-wordpress-site-backWPup-wordpress-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"how-to-backup-your-wordpress-site-backWPup-wordpress-plugin\" width=\"750\" height=\"418\" /></a></p><p><a title=\"BackWPup\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/backwpup/\" target=\"_blank\">BackWPup</a> is a popular WordPress backup plugin that helps&nbsp;you to create complete backups of your WordPress site, and save the same on an external location such as Dropbox, Amazon S3, FTP, RackSpace Cloud and many more.</p><p>You can schedule full backups meaning your entire WordPress site, files and all, will be safe always. Further you can check/repair and optimize your database, and if you need more juice, you can go for the pro version. The plugin has more than 400K active installs.</p><h3>WordPress Backup to Dropbox Free WordPress Plugin</h3><p><a title=\"WordPress Backup To Dropbox\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-backup-to-dropbox/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-36121\" title=\"How To Backup Your WordPress Site WordPress Backup To Dropbox Plugin\" src=\"http://mainwpex.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/how-to-backup-your-wordpress-site-wordpress-backup-to-dropbox-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"how-to-backup-your-wordpress-site-wordpress-backup-to-dropbox-plugin\" width=\"750\" height=\"427\" /></a></p><p>Here&rsquo;s a WordPress backup plugin that forces you to make use of that Dropbox account that&rsquo;s been lying around. <a title=\"WordPress Backup To Dropbox\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-backup-to-dropbox/\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress Backup to Dropbox</a> has a rating of 3.9/5.0 and over 100K active installs. In a matter of minutes, you can set up the plugin to send full backups to your Dropbox account. Just install the plugin, set up a schedule and authenticate your Dropbox account. Simple as A, B, C.</p><h3>UpdraftPlus Backup and Restoration Free WordPress Plugin</h3><p><a title=\"UpdraftPlus\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/updraftplus/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-36122\" title=\"How To Backup Your WordPress Site Updraftplus WordPress Backup Plugin\" src=\"http://mainwpex.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/how-to-backup-your-wordpress-site-updraftplus-wordpress-backup-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"how-to-backup-your-wordpress-site-updraftplus-wordpress-backup-plugin\" width=\"750\" height=\"420\" /></a></p><p>One of the highest-ranked WordPress backup plugin, <a title=\"UpdraftPlus\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/updraftplus/\" target=\"_blank\">UpdraftPlus</a> adds fun and ease to backing up your WordPress site. With a number of sweet features including backups to Amazon S3, Google Drive, FTP, Dropbox, email and other storage options, quick restore, scheduling, site duplicator, capability to split large sites into multiple archives, and so much more, you can&rsquo;t go wrong with UpdraftPlus.</p><p>This WordPress backup plugin has an impressive rating of 4.9/5.0 and over 500K active installs. They offer a pro version that packs quite a punch.</p><h3>BackupBuddy Premium WordPress Plugin</h3><p><a title=\"BackupBuddy By IThemes\" href=\"http://www.wpexplorer.com/out/backupbuddy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-36123\" title=\"How To Backup Your WordPress Site Backupbuddy Plugin\" src=\"http://mainwpex.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/how-to-backup-your-wordpress-site-backupbuddy-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"how-to-backup-your-wordpress-site-backupbuddy-plugin\" width=\"750\" height=\"421\" /></a></p><p>The only premium WordPress backup plugin on our list today, <a title=\"BackupBuddy By iThemes\" href=\"http://www.wpexplorer.com/out/backupbuddy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">BackupBuddy by iThemes</a> is an industry leader. You can use the plugin to create full database and files backup, and/or move your site to another server easily.</p><p>You can backup your site to your hard disk and a variety of external storage services including Amazon Web Services, Rackspace, email, FTP, Dropbox, and BackupBuddy Stash among others.</p><p>Schedule backups on the go and enjoy a backup service like no other. Price ranges between $80 and $150 per year. They also offer a lifetime Gold package at a one-time fee of $297, so choose a solution that&rsquo;s fit for your business.</p><h2>&nbsp;</h2>';
		$task->user_id = 1;
